## Title:	.nanorc
## Author:	rvare (on GitHub)
## Purpose:	This file is to make Gnu Nano look and feel like other editors, such as vim and emacs.
## But also, to illustrate how Nano can look and feel differently.
include "/usr/share/nano/*.nanorc"
## set nohelp ## Set when you don't want the help menu
set linenumbers
set indicator
set autoindent
set minibar
set tabsize 4
set numbercolor lightwhite
set constantshow
set smarthome
set multibuffer
set softwrap
set atblanks
## What it does: I auto-indenting, M mark is on, L hard-wrapping, R recording a macro, S soft-wrapping.
set stateflags
